<html
  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
  xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
  xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
  xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
  xml:lang="en"
  lang="en"
  dir="ltr"
  metal:use-macro="view/macro:page/pillarindex"
  i18n:domain="launchpad"
>
  <body>
    <h1 metal:fill-slot="heading">Registered distributions</h1>

<metal:rightportlets fill-slot="portlets_two">
  <div class="portlet">
    <h2>About these distributions</h2>

    <div class="portletBody portletContent">
      <img src="/@@/info" />
      Launchpad can manage the source packages, builds, archive publishing
      and historical record-keeping necessary to create a distribution.
      Some of the distributions described here are fully managed in
      Launchpad, others are managed elsewhere but Launchpad keeps track of
      their progress.
    </div>
  </div>
</metal:rightportlets>

<div metal:fill-slot="main">

    <div id="application-summary">
      Launchpad can keep track of the software packages in a distribution,
      and provide information about the bugs, translations and code
      associated with each of them.
    </div>

    <table class="listing">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Distribution</th>
          <th>Domain</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr tal:repeat="distribution context">
          <td>
            <img src="/@@/distribution" />
            <a tal:content="distribution/title" 
               tal:attributes="href distribution/fmt:url">
                  distribution title
            </a>
            <span tal:condition="distribution/is_read_only" class="lesser">
              *
            </span>
          </td>
          <td tal:content="distribution/domainname">
            domain.org
          </td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>    

    <p>
      <sup>*</sup> Read-only distribution.
      Can be browsed in Launchpad, but not altered or managed,
      and its information might be out of date.
    </p>

  </div>

</body>
</html>
